From Mineberg pdf find out what this command from ntpd.hotplug-helper (its contents are in the end of README) does:

        STATUS="$(/usr/sbin/ntpq -c 'rv 0 stratum'|awk -F '=' '{ print $2 }')"

and if it can be used instead of ntpq -p | grep '^\*' for checking non-initial status

------------------------

If non-gps sync will not work, try to add flag1 like for gps:

server 127.127.28.0
fudge 127.127.28.0 flag1 1

alternatively, try -g and -G options to /sbin/ntpd

------------------

Find out from dnsmasq source what does this command from /etc/hotplug.d/ntp/25-dnsmasqsec (its contents are below),
which is called by '/sbin/hotplug-call ntp':

    procd_send_signal dnsmasq '*' INT

--------------------------------------------------------

#!/bin/sh

. /lib/functions/procd.sh

TIMEVALIDFILE="/var/state/dnsmasqsec"

[ "$ACTION" = stratum ] || exit 0

[ -f "$TIMEVALIDFILE" ] || {
	echo "ntpd says time is valid" >$TIMEVALIDFILE
	/etc/init.d/dnsmasq enabled && {
		procd_send_signal dnsmasq '*' INT
	}
}
